{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum Hamming weight of the product of a constant (2023) and an integer n. This is equivalent to finding the minimum number of ones in the binary representation of a multiple of 2023. This is a problem of finding the smallest weight of a multiple of a given integer in base 2.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Find the prime factorization of 2023 and express it in terms of its binary properties. Specifically, identify if 2023 is coprime to 2 and determine its value modulo powers of 2 or its relationship to Mersenne numbers (2^m - 1)."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Investigate the existence of an integer n such that 2023*n is a power of 2 minus 1 (a Mersenne number) or a sum of very few powers of 2. Test if 2023 divides 2^m - 1 for small m, or if 2023 divides 2^m + 2^j + 1, etc., to find the minimum number of ones."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_3",
      "instructions": "Verify if k(n) = 1 is possible (this requires 2023 to be a power of 2, which it is not) and if k(n) = 2 is possible (this requires 2023 to divide 2^a + 2^b for some a, b). If k(n) = 2 is impossible, test if k(n) = 3 is possible by checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + 2^c."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent will use the prime factorization to confirm 2023 is odd. It will then use the results from the helpers to rule out k(n)=1 and k(n)=2 by checking divisibility of 2^a + 2^b by 2023. Finally, it will use the findings from the search for k(n)=3 to determine if the minimum is 2 or 3 (or higher) and provide the final integer."
}

